texts: This is Rhino Leader. Just passed through Mejiro.
72 minutes ago, Charlie Two spotted the target in front of Kanda Station.
The target escaped before they could get her attention, though. There has been no contact with her since.
How'd a non-combatant slip through? I know we didn't want this mission, but we still gotta take it seriously.
Apologies. It turns out that the target has better intuition than we'd bargained for.
We confirmed that the target took a self-driving taxi near Jinbocho.
According to the taxi's logs, she was dropped off near Tetsugakudo Park in Nakano.
Then, 14 minutes ago, she walked by a convenience store near Numabukuro Station.
We used AI prediction to narrow down the routes she could have taken from there.
Now we're having data satellites track those routes. 80 seconds until preparations are complete.
Bravo, split into three groups and wait for the target ahead.
Charlie, search north of Numabukuro Station, just in case.
Alpha and I'll follow the predicted routes to the south.
Narashino, keep up the search. Rhino Leader, out.
